## Distance Vector & Multicast Routing Simulation

This project implements a distance-vector routing protocol and a multicast routing protocol for unidirectional networks using C and UNIX process-based simulation.

Each network node runs as a concurrent process and communicates through file-based channels, while a controller enforces topology constraints. The routing layer uses flooded distance-vector and in-distance messages to compute paths, and the multicast layer builds and maintains source-based trees with dynamic join, failure detection, and recovery.

